---Event Management System---

=>Project Description

EventSphere is a frontend Event Management Application developed using modern JavaScript (ES6+), modular architecture, and JSON Server as a fake REST API.

The system allows administrators to manage events and users to view and register for events. The application follows separation of concerns using Models, Services, Controllers, and Utilities.

This project demonstrates real-world concepts such as OOP, Async/Await, ES6 Modules, Form Validation, and CRUD operations without page reload.

=>Features Implemented

=>Admin Module

* Add new event
* View all events
* Delete event
* Seat availability tracking
* Event form validation

=>User Module

* View available events
* View event details
* Register for an event
* Seat count decreases after registration
* Registration form validation
* Success and error messages

=>Business Rules Implemented

* Available seats decrease after successful registration
* Registration blocked if no seats available
* Capacity must be positive
* Date cannot be past date
* Proper error handling with try/catch
* No page reload during CRUD operations


=>Technologies Used

* HTML5
* CSS3
* Bootstrap (UI Styling)
* JavaScript (ES6+)
* ES6 Modules (import/export)
* JavaScript Classes (OOP)
* Async/Await
* Fetch API
* JSON Server (Fake REST API)


